Do’s
Do maintain a professional tone on public posts.
Do think before sharing any content—consider long-term impact.
Do credit sources when sharing academic information.
Do adjust privacy settings to protect personal information.
Do use social media to build a positive personal and academic brand.
Don’ts
Don’t post offensive, discriminatory, or insensitive content.
Don’t share private college or work-related information publicly.
Don’t engage in online arguments or impulsive comments.
Don’t share unverified news or misinformation.
Don’t upload photos or videos that could harm your reputation.
